model.hed: See Badass Models Ride Skateboards at Ashish's Confetti-Filled Fashion Show
model.dek: This might be the coolest fashion show we've seen all season.

items.caption: Ashish designer Ashish Gupta always has a surprise (or two!) in store for the runway, but this season might just be our favorite yet. At yesterday's Spring 2016 fashion show, models came out on skateboards sporting the season's sheer, layered confetti-covered looks. It was the perfect way to close London Fashion week, with a total bang.
Playing peek-a-boo in a long trench and sheer embellished top.
Making the case for nose piercings — these girls make it look too cool for school.
The confetti party even continues on the kaleidoscopic nails.
Sneaker game strong.
It may not be an everyday beauty look, but it's definitely one we're going to try.
Pretty in pink.
Definitive proof that [separates](http://www.teenvogue.com/story/sarah-hyland-teen-choice-awards-red-carpet-outfit) can look just as fancy as a dress.
Peace, love, confetti. That's how the saying goes, right?
Serious star power.
It's all love with these backstage besties.
This takes wearing your heart on your sleeve to a whole new level.
These nails would instantly brighten anyone's look.
Ethereal beauties minutes before they hit the runway.
Girl skaters are the coolest.
This skirt was made for twirling.
On Wednesdays, we wear pink.
Making Miley proud.
A convincing case for getting bangs.
Confetti Crew - 2016.

fields.name: Alexandra Thurmond
fields.bio:
__What sort of advice would you give your 18-year-old self?__  
I would tell myself to try as many different things as possible! College is an amazing time to experiment, indulge your interests, and find out what you’re truly passionate about.

__What fashion item seems to always be on your shopping list?__  
I’ve never met an awesome pair of wide leg (preferably printed) pants that I didn’t love—they’ve become my signature. Bring on the palazzos!
 
__What’s your go-to karaoke song?__  
No Doubt “Just a Girl” - Tragic Kingdom was the first CD I ever owned. I’ve always wanted to be Gwen Stefani, she is such a strong female figure and all around badass.

__What’s your favorite movie quote?__  
"It’s all happening.” From band-aid Penny Lane in Almost Famous (my all-time favorite movie!). She was all about living in the moment and never taking experiences for granted.
fields.title: Digital Fashion Editor
